# Agent Shield: mandatory agent onboarding

Before writing a single line of code or editing any file, read these files in order:

1. `CONTEXT.md` — full local project state (gitignored; read only when it exists in the working directory)
2. `SESSION_STATE.md` — parallel-session coordination (combine with `CONTEXT.md`; workstreams, files in flight)
3. `AGENT_SHIELD_TODO.md` — atomic execution checklist (single source of truth)
4. `CLAUDE.md` — project rules, conventions, response behavior

Skip none. All four together take under a few minutes and prevent rework from stale context.

## Before stopping any session

Update `AGENT_SHIELD_TODO.md` (check off items that landed), `CONTEXT.md` if private state shifted, and `SESSION_STATE.md` if parallel work would be confused without an update. There is no dated milestone calendar in `TIMELINES.md` — only the checklist matters.

## Contributor rule

Aditya is the sole contributor. No AI agent credited as author, co-author, or contributor anywhere — commit messages, PR descriptions, comments, or doc footers. See `CLAUDE.md` Rule A.
